{"TRIQUADRANTAL":[{"def":"Having three quadrants; thus, a triquadrantal triangle is one whose three sides are quadrants, and whose three angles are consequently right angles.","pos":""}],"TRIQUETROUS":[{"def":"Three sided, the sides being plane or concave; having three salient angles or edges; trigonal.","pos":""}],"TRIQUETRUM":[{"def":"One of the bones of the carpus; the cuneiform.","pos":""},{"def":"Having three rays.","pos":""}]}